<h3>Why RCEP ?</h3>
<ul>
<li>Lower tariffs</li>
<li>Open up trade and services</li>
<li>Promote Investment</li>
<li>Reduce cost and time for companies</li></ul>
<h3>India not join, <strong>concerns</strong>?</h3>
<ul>
<li>Chinese goods would flood Indian Markets- due to tariff reduction + chinese overcapacity due to US-CHINA tension</li>
<li>
<p>Hamper domestic industries</p></li>
<li>
<p>Ratchet clauses and base year of 2014 (India says 2019)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Rules of origin not defined</p></li>
<li>
<p>ICT and services integration not enough</p></li>
<li>
<p>New Zealand and Australia milk flood (Flourishing Dairy of these would affect Indian milk&nbsp;producers)</p></li>
<li>
<p>&nbsp;</p></li></ul>
<h3>WHY INDIA SHOULD JOIN RCEP ?</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Suhasini Haider</strong>
<ul>
<li>India needs to sign separate TAs with countries
<ul>
<li>Japan- CEPA</li>
<li>South Korea- CECA</li>
<li>ASEAN -FTA</li>
<li>No TA with Aus since 2011</li>
<li>Aus, China, NZ - Joined RCEP (They will given prominence to RCEP;&nbsp;RCEP&gt; India)</li></ul></li>
<li>Regional Agreements is the new normal
<ul>
<li>NAFTA- NA</li>
<li>Southern Common Market/ MERCOSUR- South America</li>
<li>EU</li>
<li>EEU- Eurasian Economic Union</li>
<li>AfCFTA</li>
<li>GCC</li>
<li>India- not a part of any except-
<ul>
<li>SAARC- Failure</li>
<li>BIMSTEC- Stagnant</li></ul></li></ul></li>
<li><strong>ACT EAST POLICY ?</strong>
<ul>
<li>As India left RCEP- It is now "China led RCEP"; USA not a part</li>
<li>Act East Policy at crossroads</li></ul></li>
<li><strong>2/4 QUAD members are part of RCEP</strong>= Japan and Aus</li>
<li>If join RCEP =&gt; integration with Global Value Chains (regional value chains)</li>
<li>FTA utilisation improves (actual vs expected benefit from FTA)&nbsp;</li></ul></li></ul>
